  "title": "Epilepsy-iEEG-Interictal-Multicenter-Dataset",
  "description": "A multicenter interictal intracranial EEG dataset from subjects with epilepsy, comprising de-identified recordings from the National Institute of Health, Johns Hopkins Hospital, and University of Miami Florida Jackson Memorial Hospital. The dataset includes annotated sleep and awake states and serves as a resource for investigating electrophysiological markers of epileptogenicity, including source-sink connectivity and high-frequency oscillations. Processed derivatives from source-sink analysis and HFO detection using RMS and Hilbert methods are provided.",
  "methods_description": "Intracranial EEG recordings were collected during interictal periods from subjects with epilepsy across multiple clinical centers. Data were de-identified and organized according to BIDS and iEEG-BIDS specifications using MNE-BIDS. Sleep and awake states were annotated where available. High-frequency oscillations were detected using both RMS and Hilbert transform methods.",
